	<h1>Our Activities</h1>
	<p>
		The Movies and Dramatics Club offers a variety of activities to engage and
		inspire our members. Whether you're interested in acting, directing, or
		working behind the scenes, there's something for everyone. Here are some of
		the key activities we offer:
	</p>
	<h2>Acting Workshops</h2>
	<p>
		Our acting workshops are designed to help members develop their acting
		skills and learn new techniques. Led by experienced actors and directors,
		these workshops cover everything from basic acting exercises to advanced
		performance skills.
	</p>
	<h2>Stage Productions</h2>
	<p>
		We stage a variety of productions throughout the year, including plays,
		skits, and musicals. These productions provide opportunities for members to
		showcase their talents and gain valuable experience in front of an audience.
	</p>
	<h2>Collaborations</h2>
	<p>
		We frequently collaborate with other clubs and organizations to produce
		unique and exciting events. These collaborations allow our members to
		broaden their horizons and work with a diverse range of performers and
		creators.
	</p>
	<h2>Social Events</h2>
	<p>
		Our social events are a great way for members to build friendships and
		create lasting memories. From informal gatherings to themed parties, we
		offer a variety of social events throughout the year.
	</p>
	<h2>Competitions</h2>
	<p>
		We participate in and organize various competitions, both within the
		university and externally. These competitions provide a platform for our
		members to test their skills and gain recognition for their talents.
	</p>
	<h2>Workshops and Masterclasses</h2>
	<p>
		In addition to our regular activities, we host special workshops and
		masterclasses with industry professionals. These sessions offer members the
		chance to learn from the best and gain insights into the world of
		professional theatre and film.
	</p>
</div>